だらしない: slovenly; loose; untidy; careless
安易 (an’i): easy; simple; easy-going
まごまご: confused; flustered; at a loss
真っ先に (massaki ni): at the very beginning; first of all
やむを得ない (yamu o enai): cannot be helped; unavoidable
いっせいに: simultaneously; all at once
スカーフ: scarf
順番に (junban ni): in turns; in number order
尊重 (sonchou): respect; esteem; regard
じきに: immediately; directly; soon; shortly
休暇 (kyuuka): holiday; day off
手頃 (tegoro): moderate; handy; convenient
手前 (temae): before; this side; one’s standpoint
手入れ (teire): care; looking after; repair; tending
手当て (teate): salary; pay; allowance; medical care
情けは人のためならず (nasake wa hito no tame narazu): the good you do for others is good you do yourself, compassion is not for other people’s benefit
つねづね: always, usually
当てにする (ate ni suru): to count on, to expect someone to (provide help, etc.)
選り好み (yorigonomi): being particular about
楽天的 (rakutenteki): optimistic
強烈 (kyouretsu): strong, intense, severe
倍増 (baizou): double
費やす (tsuiyasu): to spend, to consume, to waste
好循環 (koujunkan): virtuous cycle, virtuous circle